  "doc_id": "55289",
  "text": "Generally, peak transmittance reduction results from nonlinear growth of intracavity absorption. Under nanosecond pulses, both 2PA itself and additional absorption of 2PA-generated free carriers play a role [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The blue spectral shift results from a negative change in the real refractive index of the intracavity layer. This change is proportional to the spatial density of photo-induced free carriers with the coefficient σ r 7 · 10 −21 cm 3 [CITATION_3] . Free carriers can be generated as a result of either 2PA or residual linear absorption by impurities in GaAs.",
